<Post
  title="Distributed compute — eleven laptops, one TCP port, and a scheduled task"
  date="2026-04-19"
  activeTab="deep-dive"
  headings={headings}
>
  <p class="deck">
    Eleven Windows laptops run an actor proxy each. One PPO learner runs on
    my desk. They talk over a single TCP port on the home LAN. This post is
    what the compute actually looks like today — numbers, configs, and the
    wire.
  </p>

